Q3

Given

const users = [
    { id: 1, name: "Ali" },
    { id: 2, name: "Sara" },
    { id: 3, name: "Hamza" }
];

Create a lookup so that finding the user with id = 2 is O(1) instead of scanning the array every time.


solution:

const users = [
    { id: 1, name: "Ali" },
    { id: 2, name: "Sara" },
    { id: 3, name: "Hamza" }
];

const usersMap = users.reduce((acc, user) => {
  acc[user.id] = user;
  return acc;
}, {});

console.log(usersMap);
